<task id="125" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add evidence-sufficiency precheck in Path 3 (PATTERN ONLY — do NOT reuse Insights EvidenceSufficiencyNode per architecture §5.2.4)</title>
    <phase>6: WP6 Specialized Playbooks + Path 3</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>123</dependencies>
    <blocks>132</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, services, architecture-binding</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies Path 3 engine (.cs); architecture §5.2.4 binding-NEGATIVE rule applies (MUST NOT reuse Insights EvidenceSufficiencyNode); FULL per task-execute Step 0.5</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>6-D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-45: add an evidence-sufficiency precheck in Path 3 (`ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync`) that returns a structured Decline shape when RAG retrieval yields 0 chunks for the requested files — avoiding garbage-summary on empty input. Per architecture §5.2.4 (binding-NEGATIVE): this is PATTERN-LEVEL inspiration only. DO NOT reuse Insights `EvidenceSufficiencyNode` — that is a playbook-execution decision gate for Insights synthesis, different domain. Build a clean, tool-level error return in the engine.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF AI engineer. Knows the Insights/Chat architecture boundary (architecture §5).</role>

  <goal>
    `ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` invokes a lightweight evidence-sufficiency check BEFORE the LLM call: if RAG retrieval for the requested `fileIds` returns 0 chunks, the engine emits a structured Decline (`{ status: "declined", reason: "no_evidence", message: "No content was found in the referenced files for this query.", fileIds: [...] }`) and short-circuits — no LLM call, no streaming. Unit test for empty-corpus case asserts Decline shape. Architecture §5.2.4 boundary respected (no Insights reuse).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-45 + architecture §5.2.4 binding-NEGATIVE rule. Insights Engine has an `EvidenceSufficiencyNode` (action type 100) — a playbook decision gate that aborts Insights synthesis when KPI assessments fall below threshold. That's the WRONG abstraction for chat-Summarize: chat needs a TOOL-LEVEL error return, not a playbook gate. Architecture §5.2.4 forbids reuse. Build the chat-specific precheck in the engine.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="architecture-§5.2.4">DO NOT reuse Insights `EvidenceSufficiencyNode` for memory recall or chat-Summarize evidence checks. Build clean recall-tool error returns instead.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Decline returned via the streaming side-channel mechanism if applicable; otherwise as a non-streaming structured response. Do NOT mid-stream abort.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stay within `Services/Ai/` boundary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Decline payload tier-1 safe — deterministic IDs only, no user content; `reason` field is enum-like, not free-text user content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-45 acceptance — empty-corpus test returns Decline shape with reason.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-06 — Insights Engine non-interference; this precheck is pattern-inspired from §5.2.4 but the implementation is chat-domain-specific.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
