      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md §5.2.4 end-to-end. Internalize the binding-NEGATIVE rule.</step>
    <step order="2">Inspect existing RAG retrieval pattern in `PlaybookExecutionEngine` and `RagService` — how `fileIds` map to AI Search query and chunk count.</step>
    <step order="3">Decide the precheck location: BEFORE the LLM call, AFTER RAG retrieval has populated the per-file context. If retrieval is currently inline with prompt assembly, refactor so chunk count is observable separately.</step>
    <step order="4">Author the Decline shape: `{ status: "declined", reason: "no_evidence", message: string, fileIds: string[] }`. Keep message templated (no user content interpolation).</step>
    <step order="5">Add the precheck: `if (totalChunks == 0) return Decline(...)`. Verify it returns ABOVE the streaming initiation point so we don't emit a half-formed SSE stream.</step>
    <step order="6">Add structured-log "precheck.declined" at info level with `reason` + count + fileIds (tier-1 safe).</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit test: arrange a mock RAG service that returns empty chunks; act on `ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync`; assert Decline shape returned (status, reason, fileIds).</step>
    <step order="8">Write unit test for positive case: chunks present → no Decline; LLM call proceeds (mock the LLM).</step>
    <step order="9">Code-grep verification: confirm zero references to `EvidenceSufficiencyNode` or `IEvidenceSufficiencyNode` introduced in this commit. (NFR-06 compliance.)</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="11">Measure BFF publish size; report delta.</step>
    <step order="12">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 FULL gates).</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 125 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs, RagService.cs, architecture §5.2.4</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply precheck + unit tests</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Verify zero EvidenceSufficiencyNode references introduced</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs — evidence-sufficiency precheck added</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEnginePrecheckTests.cs — new tests</output>
