  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Empty-corpus unit test returns Decline with `reason: "no_evidence"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Positive case unit test proceeds to LLM call.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`grep "EvidenceSufficiencyNode" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs` returns ZERO hits (architecture §5.2.4 boundary respected).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Trace log emits "precheck.declined" tier-1 safe.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Decline returned BEFORE any SSE stream initiation (no half-stream).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish delta reported.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Architecture §5.2.4 is BINDING. The pattern is inspired by Insights but the IMPLEMENTATION must be chat-domain-specific — different timing (pre-LLM, not post-synthesis), different consumer (engine short-circuit, not playbook abort), different return shape (Decline vs Insights AbortPlaybook). If a reviewer asks "why not reuse EvidenceSufficiencyNode?" the answer is architecture §5.2.4.
  </notes>

